commText: Rahul and Arshin Kulkarni are at the crease. Rahul is on strike. Vaibhav Arora will open the attack

Vaibhav Arora to Rahul, FOUR, KL gets off the mark with a boundary! Hint on shape away from the right-hander, decent bounce as well, Rahul opens his bat-face and guides it expertly between short third man and backward point
Vaibhav Arora to Rahul, 1 run, inswinger, fuller in length and Rahul pushes towards mid-off for a quick single
Two fielders outside the circle - deep backward square leg and long-on. One slip in place
Vaibhav Arora to Arshin Kulkarni, no run, 136.5kph, inswinger, Arshin Kulkarni presses forward to tap it to cover
Vaibhav Arora to Arshin Kulkarni, 1 run, full again but the line is too straight, Arshin Kulkarni flicks it towards long leg to get off the mark
Vaibhav Arora to Rahul, 1 run, inswinger, leg-lined, helped on its way to fine leg

Vaibhav Arora to Arshin Kulkarni, FOUR, lovely shot! Full inswinger and Arshin Kulkarni plays a sumptuous straight drive. A forward press and he offers a vertical bat to stroke it down the ground. That should give a lot of confidence for the 19-year-old!
Mitchell Starc, Left-arm fast, comes into the attack
Starc to Rahul, FOUR, 141.2kph, Starc greeted with a boundary. Full delivery with a hint of inswing, Rahul gets forward and opens his bat-face to play a superb square drive. Glorious!
Starc to Rahul, 1 run, 141.9kph, full and swinging in, flicked to the right of mid-on
Starc to Arshin Kulkarni, FOUR, in the air and in the gap! 143.9kph, inswinger, Arshin Kulkarni closes his bat-face and uppishly clips it between mid-on and midwicket
Starc to Arshin Kulkarni, no run, 146.4kph, length ball that goes away with the angle, Arshin Kulkarni plays inside the line to let it pass
Starc to Arshin Kulkarni, no run, 139.8kph, fuller than a length, pushed with hard hands towards cover
Starc to Arshin Kulkarni, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Starc to Arshin Kulkarni, out Caught by Ramandeep Singh!! Ramandeep Singh takes a stunning catch! 139.2kph, length ball, Arshin Kulkarni shapes to flick and the ball lobs up off the leading edge and it looked like that the ball would land between the two converging fielders (cover and deep backward point). However, Ramandeep had other ideas. He covers a lot of distance running back from cover, keeps his eyes on the ball and times his dive perfectly to take a two-handed stunner. Arshin Kulkarni c Ramandeep Singh b Starc 9(7) [4s-2]
Marcus Stoinis, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Vaibhav Arora to Rahul, no run, Rahul has been given out, caught down the leg-side. The LSG captain reviews it. Short of length just down leg, Rahul looks to flick and the ball brushes the thigh pad before going to the keeper who takes a diving catch to his left. Flat line on UltraEdge when the ball crosses the bat. No bat and it's a successful review
Vaibhav Arora to Rahul, 2 runs, 133.4kph, length ball, tucked through square leg
Vaibhav Arora to Rahul, wide, 137.4kph, full and down leg, Rahul misses the flick
Vaibhav Arora to Rahul, no run, 135.5kph, dabbed to backward point
Vaibhav Arora to Rahul, 1 run, 133.4kph, inswinger, pushed towards midwicket for a quick single

Vaibhav Arora to Stoinis, SIX, 138kph, short and wide of off with short third man inside the circle. A hopping Stoinis upper-cuts it over third man. The ball boy takes the catch - good technique there...
Vaibhav Arora to Stoinis, no run, head-high bouncer, Stoinis half-ducks
Starc to Rahul, 1 run, 142.8kph, full wide of off, Rahul looks to smash it through the off-side and gets an inside edge which eludes the leg-stump and rolls towards the keeper
Starc to Stoinis, FOUR, 142.4kph, too much width and Stoinis slaps the cut over the leaping cover point fielder. Bullets away to the fence
Starc to Stoinis, no run, 143.3kph, full and pushed across the right-hander, Stoinis throws his bat at it and gets beaten on the outside edge
Starc to Stoinis, FOUR, 144.7kph, pitched up outside off, Stoinis clears his front leg to smash it over wide mid-off. Good contact on this occasion
Starc to Stoinis, FOUR, third boundary of the over! 138.6kph, shorter and wider, Stoinis hangs back and throws his arms to flay the cut through point. Reaches the fence in a jiffy
Starc switches to round the wicket
Starc to Stoinis, no run, in-slanting short of a good length ball from round the wicket and Stoinis punches it to backward point
Spin time! No slip....
Sunil Narine, right-arm off break, comes into the attack
Narine to Rahul, no run, 92.1kph, starts with an offie does Narine and Rahul watchfully pushes it towards midwcket
Narine to Rahul, no run, Rahul skips down the track to flick over midwicket, gets beaten on the inside edge and is rapped on the pads. Salt appeals for lbw but the batter was too far down the pitch
Narine to Rahul, wide, spinning down leg, good grab by the keeper
Narine to Rahul, 2 runs, non-turner, skiddy ball, Rahul rocks back to cut to the left of cover who dives and gets a hand on it to save a couple of runs
Narine to Rahul, no run, length ball around off, punched off the back foot but straight to cover point
Narine to Rahul, no run, touch fuller, Rahul backs away to slap it hard, but he can't find the gap through the covers
Narine to Rahul, 1 run, gently turned to square leg for a single. Just 4 runs off Narine's opening over
Harshit Rana, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Harshit Rana to Rahul, 1 run, 137.7kph, fuller than a length around off, Rahul shuffles to shovel it between mid-on and midwicket. Brings his bottom hand into play but couldn't get it past mid-on
Harshit Rana to Stoinis, no run, 115.9kph, slower ball, very full and Stoinis pushes it back to the bowler
Mitchell Starc in powerplay this IPL Overs: 22 Conceded: 245 Wickets: 6 ER: 11.13
Harshit Rana to Stoinis, SIX, 136.8kph, short ball down leg and Stoinis swivels across and helps it on it way over fine leg with a hook shot!
Harshit Rana to Stoinis, no run, 141.6kph, back of a length on off, punched to backward point
Harshit Rana to Stoinis, wide, slower delivery, dips, but the line is down leg, beats Stoinis's flick
Harshit Rana to Stoinis, no run, that's a peach from Harshit Rana! 139.5kph, in-slanting short of a good length ball that hits the deck and seams away to beat the outside edge of Stoinis
Harshit Rana to Stoinis, no run, 142.9kph, back of a length ball angled in, Stoinis hops and blocks. 55 runs is the second-highest total in powerplay for LSG in this IPL season

Over Summary (1-6) -- Vaibhav concedes 11 off the opening over -- Ramandeep takes a stunner to dismiss Arshin Kulkarni -- Rahul given out on 11 (strangle down leg), survives on review -- Narine bowls a tight over to regain momentum -- Harshit Rana bowls 4 dots in the last over of the powerplay
Narine to Rahul, 1 run, quick through the air and full on middle and leg, knocked down to long-on
Most wickets taken in powerplay in IPL 2024 21 - KKR* 20 - GT 19 - LSG 18 - RR 17 - DC
Narine to Stoinis, 2 runs, on a back of a length on off, goes straight on, Stoinis punches it down the ground. Long-on moves to his left to cut it off. A couple results
Narine to Stoinis, 1 run, turning towards the hips from a back of a length, tucked round the corner for a run
Narine to Rahul, 1 run, floated delivery outside off, Rahul kneels down on one knee and sweeps it to short fine for a brisk single
Narine to Stoinis, FOUR, shot! A half-volley outside off, Stoinis leans into it and smashes it through extra cover for a rocketing boundary. He is in the zone
Narine to Stoinis, 1 run, quicker and flatter, Stoinis hangs back and tucks it to deep mid-wicket to retain strike
Harshit Rana to Stoinis, 1 run, back of a length ball angling in on middle and leg, Stoinis backs away a bit and flat-bats it towards long-on

Harshit Rana to Rahul, FOUR, the 50-run stand comes up between the duo! A short of length ball outside off, Rahul shuffles a bit and swipes it through square leg. The fielder in the deep runs to his left but has no chance to cut it off
Harshit Rana to Rahul, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Harshit Rana to Rahul, out Caught by Ramandeep Singh!! Rahul holes out! Good field placement from Shreyas Iyer and KKR reap the reward. A fuller length ball and a bit of width on offer, Rahul throws his bat at it as he slashes it towards deep point. Ramandeep is standing 15 metres in front of the boundary ropes. He doesn't need to move as the ball comes straight at his throat and he takes it reverse cup. He had timed that well but couldn't find the gap. Rahul c Ramandeep Singh b Harshit Rana 25(21) [4s-3]
Deepak Hooda, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Harshit Rana to Hooda, FOUR, Hooda doesn't need any sighters! A full ball angling towards the pads, Hooda stays nicely balanced and whips it over mid-wicket for a boundary. Almost went all the way

Harshit Rana to Hooda, 1 run, did that carry? A length ball angling in, perhaps sticks a bit on the surface, Hooda pushes at it with hard hands but ends up chipping it back towards Harshit Rana. He dives in front in his followthrough and might have got fingertips to it. Can call it a half-chance but was very difficult
Harshit Rana to Stoinis, 1 run, pitched up outside off, Stoinis strokes it down to long-off
Varun Chakaravarthy, right-arm leg break, comes into the attack
Chakaravarthy to Stoinis, 1 run, turning in from a back of a length on off, Stoinis works it to deep mid-wicket
Chakaravarthy to Hooda, THATS OUT!! Lbw!!

Chakaravarthy to Hooda, out Lbw!! Hooda has been trapped in front but he opts for the review! Looked quite adjacent to the naked eye. Was a length ball that turned in from outside off, Hooda played all around it as he missed the line to get struck on the pads. Time for the replays. Over to ball-tracking. Impact is in front of middle and hitting is umpire's call. It would have hit the top of leg. KKR on top. Hooda lbw b Chakaravarthy 5(3) [4s-1]
Deepak Hooda in IPL 2024 Inns: 7 Runs: 134 Avg: 22.33 SR: 142.5 HS: 50

Time for the strategic break! KKR have struck in quick succession to get rid of Rahul and Hooda and that has put even more pressure on LSG. The hosts have an uphill task in front of them. Can someone play a blinder to take them close?
Nicholas Pooran, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Chakaravarthy to Pooran, SIX, take that, Chakaravarthy! Was in the slot for Pooran. He got into a good position, cleared his front leg, and smoked it over long-on for a huge maximum
Chakaravarthy to Pooran, 1 run, quicker and flatter outside off, Pooran mistimes his flat-batted stroke through mid-on
Chakaravarthy to Stoinis, 1 run, full and drifting in from outside off, Stoinis sweeps it towards deep mid-wicket
Chakaravarthy to Pooran, no run, on a length and turning across Pooran. He chases it as he throws his bat at it but gets an edge. It strikes Philip Salt on the bottom of his left leg and rolls behind
Andre Russell, right-arm fast, comes into the attack
Russell to Stoinis, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Russell to Stoinis, out Caught by Harshit Rana!! Russell strikes first ball! Ravi Shastri on air mentions that he has got him 5 times now in 32 deliveries! A good length ball in the off-stump channel, Stoinis looked to hit it across the line but got a leading edge towards point. Rana moves to his right and gets low to take it safely. Stoinis c Harshit Rana b Russell 36(21) [4s-4 6s-2]
Ayush Badoni, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Russell to Ayush Badoni, wide, short delivery this time, Ayush Badoni sways away from it and it's been wided
Russell to Ayush Badoni, SIX, crunched! A short ball angling into Ayush Badoni. He stands tall and pulls it with aplomb over deep square leg for a maximum
Russell to Ayush Badoni, 1 run, back of a length ball angling in, Ayush Badoni turns it to deep mid-wicket
Russell to Pooran, no run, a short of length ball shaping across Pooran. He slashes at it but only meets thin air

Russell to Pooran, 1 run, a direct-hit would have been curtains for Ayush Badoni! Pooran taps the back of a length delivery towards Ramandeep at short third and the batters took off. Ayush Badoni had given up but the shy missed
Russell to Ayush Badoni, 2 runs, a yorker length ball tailing in, Ayush Badoni flicks it through mid-wicket and rushes back for the second run
Sunil Narine [2.0-0-14-0] is back into the attack
Narine to Pooran, 1 run, turning away from a back of a length on off, Pooran punches it off the inner half towards long-off
Narine to Ayush Badoni, 1 run, length ball on off, drifts away this time, Ayush Badoni hangs back and punches it against the spin to long-on
Narine to Pooran, 1 run, turning away from a length around off, Pooran slaps it to deep point
Narine to Ayush Badoni, no run, turning towards the pads, glanced to short fine. Ayush Badoni wants a single but it's not on
Narine to Ayush Badoni, no run, quick and flat outside off, Ayush Badoni with minimal foot movement bunts it back to Narine
Narine to Ayush Badoni, 1 run, on a back of a length outside off, Ayush Badoni camps back and works it with the spin to deep mid-wicket. 100 up for LSG. Another tidy over from Narine

Russell to Ayush Badoni, 1 run, dropped! A back of a length ball around off, Ayush Badoni looks to heave it across but gets a leading edge towards third man. Narine runs in, he is not charging towards the ball and doesn't even get his hands to it actually. It hit him on the toe. He could have done better
Russell to Pooran, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Russell to Pooran, out Caught by Philip Salt!! Another one bites the dust! A shortish delivery angling across Pooran. He tries to take it on as he goes for a pull across the line but gets a thick edge behind. Philip Salt leaps and takes it overhead to go up in celebration. Things going pear-shaped for LSG. Pooran c Philip Salt b Russell 10(8) [6s-1]
Nicholas Pooran vs Andre Russell in T20s Runs: 106 Balls: 72 Dismissals: 5 Avg: 21.2 SR: 147.2
Ashton Turner, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Russell to Turner, 1 run, full ball shaping towards the pads, flicked to deep square leg
Russell to Ayush Badoni, 1 run, slower back of a length ball this time, Ayush Badoni works it through mid-wicket
Russell to Turner, wide, a short ball outside off but it's too short, Turner lets it go and it's been wided
KKR review against a wide

Russell to Turner, wide, another short ball outside off and Turner let it sail through. KKR challenged the call but it looked very short. The third umpire has a look at it and signals a wide. KKR lose a review
Russell to Turner, leg byes, 1 run, full ball tailing towards leg-stump, Turner looks to flick but it deflects off his pads towards the keeper for a leg-bye
Russell to Ayush Badoni, 1 run, Ayush Badoni hangs back in the crease to the short of length delivery and turns it to deep mid-wicket to retain strike
Narine to Ayush Badoni, 1 run, slow through the air and full around off, Ayush Badoni eases it down to long-on
Narine to Turner, 1 run, Turner was shaping for a big shot but Narine cramped him. He tucks it with the spin through mid-wicket
Narine to Ayush Badoni, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Narine to Ayush Badoni, out Caught by Starc!! Narine spots Ayush Badoni using his feet and holds his length back. Badoni is not to the pitch of it but still goes through his expansive shot. Ends up slicing it towards long-off. Starc is late to pick it up but he does well to run in front and gets low to pouch it safely. Ayush Badoni c Starc b Narine 15(12) [6s-1]
Krunal Pandya, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Narine to Krunal Pandya, 1 run, quick and flat on a back of a length on off, Krunal Pandya chops it to short third off the outer half
Narine to Turner, no run, on a back of a length outside off, punched to extra cover
Narine to Turner, 1 run, on a length outside off, Turner chops it through point. End of a miserly spell from Narine
Ayush Badoni against Sunil Narine in IPL Inns: 4 Runs: 30 Balls: 30 Dismissals: 3 Avg: 10.0
Varun Chakaravarthy [1.0-0-9-1] is back into the attack
Chakaravarthy to Turner, SIX, tossed up full ball around off, Turner kneels down on one knee and slog sweeps it over deep mid-wicket for a 78m maximum. Struck that well
Chakaravarthy to Turner, 1 run, quicker and flatter outside off, chopped to covers for a run
Chakaravarthy to Krunal Pandya, no run, back of a length ball on off from round the wicket, Krunal Pandya mistimes his pull to mid-wicket
Chakaravarthy to Krunal Pandya, 1 run, on the shorter side around off, Krunal Pandya rocks back and cuts it to deep point
Chakaravarthy to Turner, SIX, smashed! In the slot outside off, Turner once again goes for the slog sweep as he crouches in his stance. Good execution and the ball sails over cow corner for a maximum
Has the inside edge deflected off Turner's foot and carried to Chakaravarthy? It's a umpire's review to check for a bump ball. OUT!
Chakaravarthy to Turner, THATS OUT!! Caught&Bowled!!

Chakaravarthy to Turner, out Caught&Bowled!! Was a quick and flat back of a length ball outside off, Turner tried to drag his flat-batted shot but got an inside edge and it seemed to have popped up off the boot. Chakaravarthy ran in front on his followthrough and took it low. The umpires took it upstairs to check for a bump ball. The replay confirms that it deflected off Turner's boot and carried cleanly to Chakaravarthy. An unfortunate dismissal but that's the way it is. Turner c and b Chakaravarthy 16(9) [6s-2]
Ashton Turner's scores in IPL 0 (1) 0 (1) 0 (1) 3* (7) 5 (9) 16 (9)
Yudhvir Singh Charak, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Harshit Rana [2.0-0-19-1] is back into the attack
Harshit Rana to Krunal Pandya, 1 run, back of a length ball around off, Krunal Pandya throws his bat at it and gets an inside edge towards fine leg
Harshit Rana to Yudhvir Singh, 1 run, back of a length ball outside off, Yudhvir Singh steers it to the right of backward point where the fielder dives to make a good stop

Harshit Rana to Krunal Pandya, 2 runs, dropped! Was a difficult chance though. A slower fullish ball outside off, Krunal Pandya mistimes his lofted stroke over mid-off. Shreyas Iyer runs back and gets both his hands to it but the ball bursts through
Harshit Rana to Krunal Pandya, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Harshit Rana to Krunal Pandya, out Caught by Philip Salt!! The wickets keep tumbling! A pacy shortish delivery angling into Krunal Pandya from round the wicket. Krunal Pandya doesn't have much space to free his arms as it gets a bit big on him. Looks to ramp it over the keeper but ends up guiding it straight to Philip Salt. He leaps to take another catch. Krunal Pandya c Philip Salt b Harshit Rana 5(6)
Ravi Bishnoi, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Harshit Rana to Ravi Bishnoi, 1 run, almost chopped on! Fullish ball around off, Ravi Bishnoi throws his bat at it but gets an inside edge past his stumps towards fine leg
Harshit Rana to Yudhvir Singh, no run, another sharp bouncer on off, Yudhvir Singh looks to pull it across but is beaten for pace
Chakaravarthy to Ravi Bishnoi, 1 run, full ball outside off, Ravi Bishnoi crouches in his stance and hits it towards long-on
Chakaravarthy to Yudhvir Singh, no run, close shave! Quick and on a fuller length around off, Yudhvir Singh looks to slog it across the line but misses. That almost took the off-pole out
Chakaravarthy to Yudhvir Singh, no run, even closer this time! Quick and flat just outside off, Yudhvir Singh looks to push and is beaten. Was agonozingly close to the off-stump
Chakaravarthy to Yudhvir Singh, SIX, slot delivery this time outside off, Yudhvir Singh tonks it over wide long-on for a maximum. Came right off the screws
Chakaravarthy to Yudhvir Singh, no run, on a back of a length outside off, tapped to covers
Chakaravarthy to Yudhvir Singh, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Chakaravarthy to Yudhvir Singh, out Caught by Russell!! Chakaravarthy has the last laugh! He bowls this one wide outside off. Yudhvir Singh has to reach out to it as he tries to hit it hard but only manages to slice it high in the air to covers. Russell moves to his left to take an easy catch. Yudhvir Singh c Russell b Chakaravarthy 7(7) [6s-1]
Time for the strategic break!
Naveen-ul-Haq, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Harshit Rana to Ravi Bishnoi, THATS OUT!! Lbw!!

Harshit Rana to Ravi Bishnoi, out Lbw!! Bishnoi has been trapped in front but he takes a chance with the review! Was a fuller length ball that shaped in from outside off, Ravi Bishnoi played all around it and missed to get hit on the back leg. UltraEdge shows a flat line. Over to ball-tracking. Hitting is umpire's call and that's good enough. KKR win by a big margin of 98 runs and go to the top of the table. Ravi Bishnoi lbw b Harshit Rana 2(3)

23:17 Local Time, 17:47 GMT, 23:17 IST: A proper lop-sided affair this one! KKR continue to go from strength-to-strength and are looking like a force to reckon with. The duo of Narine and Salt once again set things up for KKR and a couple of cameos down the order propelled KKR to a massive score. Once the visitors posted 235 on the board (highest T20 score at this venue), they had their tails up at the halfway stage. Kulkarni was nipped out by Starc quite early, courtesy a brilliant catch from Ramandeep. Rahul and Stoinis played a few eye-catchy strokes and stitched a 50-run stand. But once the former departed, things went pear-shaped for LSG as they kept losing wickets in a jiffy. There was some turn available for Narine and Chakaravarthy and they bowled with a lot of discipline. Russell took two important wickets of Stoinis and Pooran and that effectively killed the game. Rana was also on the money and picked up a 3-fer. A forgettable day at the office for LSG. Stick around for the presentations...

KL Rahul | LSG captain: It was a lot of runs to be scored in the second innings. When you are chasing a big total, you are trying to go too hard and you end up losing wickets. Just a poor performance overall. We didn't (hit our lengths on a consistent basis), just been a poor performance overall with bat, ball and in the field. Sunil Narine and Phil Salt, in the powerplay, we've seen how they bat and they do put a lot of pressure on the opposition. Our young bowlers couldn't handle that kind of pressure and he hit some really good shots. That's how IPL is, you come up against really good players and that's when your character is tested. We weren't up to the mark. The wicket was really good, felt like a pretty true wicket, there was a bit of bounce if you bowled hard lengths and back of a lengths, but nothing out of the ordinary and it didn't seem like a pitch that was really bad. 235 was probably 20 or 30 runs above par and our batting performance was really poor. When you're chasing such a big score, you're under pressure, it's always hard. We prepare well in advance and talk about the opposition batters, we know our conditions here and we do spend a little bit of time talking to the bowlers and talking to the batters trying to see what kind of plans we need to come up with. Once we come here, it's about execution and we went wrong in that part. Bowlers tried their best but the young group really ... the sooner you learn, the better it for the team. We've made a couple of mistakes when we've come up against batters like Sunil and anyone that's powerful. That type of intimidation puts pressure on our bowlers. That'll be the chat once we get back to the dressing room - move on from this game, see where we went wrong and try and get better. This is our last home game for us, so we are on the road for the next three games. It's pretty clear for us, if you want to get to the top four, you got to win all the games. That will give us a little bit of freedom to go out there and be a little bit more fearless, little bit brave to take on the game.

Harshit Rana: We don't want to take anything lightly and this is the kind of approach we want to have to make it to the playoffs. The coaches told me to focus on hitting the hard lengths and I got rewards for doing the same. I keep working on the areas that I need to improve, it becomes very handy when he (Russell) comes in and picks those wickets during the middle overs and it helps in shifting the momentum as well.

Stats by Shashikant Singh

Shreyas Iyer | KKR captain: The last 6 matches in the dressing room there has been havoc, teammates are coming in and asking skip what's happening, we are losing tosses, but we are winning games that's what matters. We had a great start in the powerplay. Sunil mentioned in the time-out that anything around 200 is good. A lefty-righty combination makes thing difficult for the opposition, the bowlers have to change their plans and that makes a difference. It's all about the freedom, to go out and express themselves. We want to go out and be positive whatever the situation is, sometimes it doesn't work out but sometimes it does. They have been splendid for us, the way they are playing their shots is pure bliss. They are setting us up and giving is momentum and no matter what the situation is, we are playing with a positive mindset.

Sunil Narine | Player of the Match: The most important thing is starting well and it's good to have the backing of the support staff. I think you have to pick your strengths and pick your spots, sometimes it works out and sometimes it doesn't. It's going very well, Varun is picking up wickets, it's making my job easier to keep things tight. He is a hard worker and it's good to see him do well. The boys are anxious and eager to play, so no matter what the situation is they are up for the challenge and they are contributing for us.

LSG were quite good at home prior to this game but received a proper thrashing at the hands of KKR tonight. They have slipped to the fifth position on the points table courtesy a 98-run loss and that has dented their net run-rate. Things are getting tight mid-table as three teams are now locked in at 12 points. Meanwhile, KKR are on a roll and have won three games in a row to rise to the top of the table. Their net run-rate has received a real boost and that augurs well for them going ahead. They have put one step into the playoffs but will be eager to keep the acceleration going. That ends our coverage for tonight. This is Abhinav Guha signing off on behalf of Abhinand Raghavendran, Raju Peethala and Praveen. Until next time, goodnight and take care!
